{"lemma":"عارِفُو","slug":"عارِفُو","root":"ع.ر.ف","root_slug":"ع-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28750"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%81%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"knowing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"acquainted, familiar (بِ (bi) with)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"expert, connoisseur"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"master"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of عَرَفَ (ʕarafa, “to know”)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.rif/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28750","headword_ar":"عَارِفٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariyfN","text_ar":"عَرِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn., (S, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlimN","text_ar":"عَالِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliymN","text_ar":"عَلِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c., agreeably with the explanations of the verb in the first quarter of the first paragraph of this art.;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwfapN","text_ar":"عَرُوفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) but in an intensive sense, which is denoted by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquainted with, affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not failing to know"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recognise"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has been seen once;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlA^umuwir","text_ar":"بِالاُمُوِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN EaruwfapN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ عَرُوفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well, acquainted with affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b2-  For the first, see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariyfN","text_ar":"عَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  It also signifies particularly ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skilled in divine things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing knowledge of God, and of his kingdom, and of the way of dealing well with Him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, the first, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Patient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very patient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much patience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabuwrN","text_ar":"صَبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AO, S, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwfN","text_ar":"عَرُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) of which latter the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSiyba fulaAnN fawujida EaArifFA","text_ar":"اُصِيبَ فُلَانٌ فَوُجِدَ عَارِفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was smitten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflicted, and was found to be patient"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habasotu nafosFA EaArifapF","text_ar":"حَبَسْتُ نَفْسًا عَارِفَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAbirapF","text_ar":"صَابِرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I restrained a patient soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA:) like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabarotu EaArifapF","text_ar":"صَبَرْتُ عَارِفَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a verse of 'Antarah [cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sbr","text_ar":"صبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, * O.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosN EaruwfN","text_ar":"نَفْسٌ عَرُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enduring; very patient; that endures an event,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a case, when made to experience it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaArifu","text_ar":"عَوَارِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArifapN","text_ar":"عَارِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Patient"},{"kind":"text","text":"she-camels. (IB, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}